<HL>
   Marketing &amp; Media:
   Mead Swaps Stock for Dataline
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   MEA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   DAYTON, Ohio -- Mead Corp. said its Dataline Inc. unit has
been acquired by Star Data Systems, a Markham, Ontario,
financial-information firm.
   Under the agreement, Star Data acquired all shares of
Dataline, a unit of Mead Data Central, in exchange for 15.1
million preferred shares of Star Data. That represents 36% of
fully diluted equity.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The preferred shares aren't publicly traded, but they can
be converted at any time into common shares on a one-for-one
basis.
   In Toronto over-the-counter trading yesterday, Star Data
common shares closed at 85 Canadian cents (73 U.S. cents).
   Dataline provides financial market information and access
to various databases.
</TEXT>
