<HL>
   Metro Airlines Traffic Climbs
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Metro Airlines said June traffic rose 38% to
59.5 million revenue passenger miles from 43 million a year
earlier. Load factor was 61.3%, up from 58.8% a year earlier.
   For the-year-to-date, the carrier said traffic rose 43% to
302.8 million revenue passenger miles from 211.7 million in
the 1989 first half.
</LP>
