<HL>
   Southwest Air's Traffic Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LUV
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Southwest Airlines said its June traffic rose
1.4% to 883.3 million revenue passenger miles from 870.9
million a year earlier. A revenue passenger mile is one
paying passenger flown one mile.
   The airline's June load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, fell to 63.9% from 68.4%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first half, traffic rose 5.8% to 4.88 billion
revenue passenger miles from 4.62 billion a year earlier.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
