   Who's News:
   Cenvill Development
   Names Martin Taplin
   To Chairman's Post
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CVL WNEWS FIAMA
</CO>
<LP>
   LAKE WORTH, Fla. -- Martin W. Taplin, a real estate
workout specialist and president of Martin W. Taplin
Associates, was named chairman of Cenvill Development Corp.,
filling a vacancy.
   Cenvill, a real estate development company, is 96%-owned
by First American Bank &amp; Trust Co. in Lake Worth and came
under control of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. when the
bank was seized by regulators last year.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Additionally, Cenvill said Jeffrey Schottenstein,
president of Schottenstein Realty Co. in Miami, and Seth
Werner, president of Werner Capital Corp., a Miami real
estate investment and management concern, were also named to
the board and designated as vice chairmen, new posts.
   The three new directors succeed Richard O'Brien, Kathryn
Kelleher and Vincent Filippini, appointees of the FDIC who
resigned. The company said the new directors were named
primarily to bolster the company's continuing efforts to find
a buyer with the help of Bear, Stearns &amp; Co.
