<HL>
   British Airways' Traffic Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BAB
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- British Airways said its June traffic rose 14%
to 3.72 billion revenue passenger miles from 3.26 billion a
year earlier. A revenue passenger mile is one paying
passenger flown one mile.
   The carrier's June load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, rose to 76% from 73.1%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the three months ended June 30, British Airways'
traffic increased 13% to 10.59 billion revenue passenger
miles from 9.35 billion a year earlier. The load factor rose
to 72.2% from 70.4%.
</TEXT>
