WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   HAN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LONDON -- Hanson PLC, a British industrial conglomerate,
said it sold its Baltimore Spice business to an affiliate of
Fuchs Gewuerze G.m.b.H., a West German seasonings and spice
maker, for $23.9 million.
   The sale includes the manufacturing operations of the Old
Bay Seasonings business, which Hanson bought in 1986 as part
of its $930 million acquisition of SCM, a U.S. conglomerate,
but Hanson will retain the retailing operations of the unit,
the company said.
</LP>
