<HL>
   Business Brief -- Kuhlman Corp.:
   Plastics Line's Sale to Unit
   Of Belgian Firm Completed
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   KUH B.SOL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Kuhlman Corp., Troy, Mich., said it completed the sale of
its plastics operations to the U.S. subsidiary of Solvay &amp;
Cie., a Brussels-based chemical corporation, in a transaction
valued at about $30.6 million plus the assumption of $14.5
million in debt and other liabilities.
   The deal leaves Kuhlman primarily a maker of electrical
transformers. The Kuhlman Plastics Group made, among other
things, plastic fuel tanks for General Motors Corp.'s
Chevrolet Corsica and Beretta cars. But Kuhlman officials
said the continuing slump in U.S. auto sales has been
reducing the profitability of the plastics operations.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The April sale agreement called for Solvay America Inc. to
pay about $24.4 million immediately, with about $6.3 million
deferred over five years. The price had been subject to
change upon the closing of the deal, but Kuhlman didn't
disclose whether the payment was altered.
   A Kuhlman spokesman said the company will elaborate on its
future plans and uses for the proceeds from the sale in a
forthcoming interim report.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>
WSJ900710-0101
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900710-0101.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Barrister Information Systems
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   BIS
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Barrister Information Systems Corp.,
which supplies computer systems to the legal profession, said
it completed an exchange of its 1989 13% subordinated
convertible debentures, due Sept. 30, 1999, in the principal
amount of $2,320,000.
   The company also said it exchanged $57,000 of its 1984 12%
subordinated convertible debentures, due Sept. 30, 1991. Both
issues were exchanged for a new 13% subordinated convertible
debenture, due June 30, 2000.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   As a result of the exchange, the company realized $794,410
in additional working capital.
