<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   FRESNO, Calif. -- WestAir Holding Inc. said its June
traffic increased 28% to 57 million revenue passenger miles
from 44.7 million a year earlier, better than expected as the
company's new Atlantic Coast Airlines and Dulles Airport hub
in Washington, D.C., performed particularly well. A revenue
passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one mile.
   The carrier's June load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, eased to 47% from 48%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first half, traffic rose 36% to 307.7 million
revenue passenger miles from 226.6 million a year earlier.
The load factor fell to 44% from 45%.
