   Business Brief -- Lazare Kaplan International Inc.:
   Jewelry Marketer Says Net
   Rose 3.3% in Its 4th Period
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   LKI
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lazare Kaplan International Inc., a New York-based
diamonds and jewelry marketer, said fiscal fourth-quarter
earnings rose 3.3% on a 23% sales gain.
   A spokesman wasn't available to elaborate on results for
the quarter ended May 31. But in a news release explaining
results for the year, Lazare Kaplan pointed to increases of
29% in sales of polished diamonds and 47% in sales of rough
diamonds. For fiscal 1990, earnings leaped 90% as sales
climbed 36%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Fourth-quarter net income rose to $2.4 million, or 74
cents a share, from $2.3 million, or 72 cents a share, a year
earlier. Net for each period includes tax-loss carry-forwards
of $768,000 and $719,000, respectively. Sales rose to $34.3
million from $28 million.
   For the year, net increased to $5.3 million, or $1.65 a
share, from $2.8 million, or 88 cents a share, in fiscal
1989. Net for each period includes tax-loss carry-forwards of
$1.7 million and $860,000, respectively. Sales advanced to
$109.7 million from $80.5 million.
